<TITLE> ACC sues CBA leader BM Bakir </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 30 (bdnews24.com) -- The Anticorruption Commission Wednesday filed a case against Sonali Bank CBA leader BM Bakir Hossain and his wife for suppressing wealth details. The commission's deputy director Md Zahangir Alam filed the case Wednesday with Motijheel Police Station. Yunus Ali, a sub-inspector of Motijheel Police Station, confirmed the news. He said the ACC alleged that the couple suppressed information in their wealth statement of Tk 1.2 crore they had earned illegally. bdn
